"children":[
{
"type":"section",
"id":"mk19_bb_id_s7_1",
"title":{
"__html":"Diagnosis"
},
"titleNode":{
"type":"section-title",
"hlId":"523223",
"children":[
"Diagnosis"
]
},
"children":[
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"3c8a97",
"children":[
"Staphylococcal ",
{
"type":"abbreviation",
"title":"toxic shock syndrome",
"children":[
"TSS"
]
},
" is associated with tampon use, nasal packings, surgical wounds, skin ulcers, burns, catheters, and injection drug use as well as:"
]
},
{
"type":"list",
"children":[
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"a3e10c",
"children":[
"fever >38.9 °C (102.0 °F)"
]
},
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"b60972",
"children":[
"systolic blood pressure <90 mm Hg"
]
},
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"45d53e",
"children":[
"diffuse macular rash with subsequent desquamation"
]
},
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"e9355f",
"children":[
"involvement of ≥3 organ systems (",
{
"type":"no-wrap",
"children":[
{
"type":"abbreviation",
"title":"gastrointestinal",
"children":[
"GI"
]
},
","
]
},
" muscular, mucous membranes, kidney, liver, blood, ",
{
"type":"abbreviation",
"title":"central nervous system",
"children":[
"CNS"
]
},
")"
]
},
" "
]
},
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"e0fcf8",
"children":[
"Streptococcal TSS is associated with necrotizing fasciitis and:"
]
},
{
"type":"list",
"children":[
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"1be218",
"children":[
"isolation of group A β-hemolytic streptococci"
]
},
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"f87dbb",
"children":[
"systolic pressure ≤90 mm Hg"
]
},
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"50bd5d",
"children":[
"two additional findings (",
{
"type":"no-wrap",
"children":[
{
"type":"abbreviation",
"title":"acute kidney injury",
"children":[
"AKI"
]
},
";"
]
},
" elevated liver enzymes; macular rash or soft tissue necrosis; coagulopathy, thrombocytopenia, ",
{
"type":"no-wrap",
"children":[
{
"type":"abbreviation",
"title":"disseminated intravascular coagulation",
"children":[
"DIC"
]
},
";"
]
},
" ",
{
"type":"abbreviation",
"title":"acute respiratory distress syndrome",
"children":[
"ARDS"
]
},
")"
]
},
" "
]
}
]
},
{
"type":"section",
"id":"mk19_bb_id_s7_2",
"title":{
"__html":"Treatment"
},
"titleNode":{
"type":"section-title",
"hlId":"4c4ac0",
"children":[
"Treatment"
]
},
"children":[
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"07e459",
"children":[
"Remove sources of infection and toxin production and begin IV fluid resuscitation. Select penicillin plus clindamycin for streptococcal TSS."
]
},
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"d3871d",
"children":[
"For methicillin-susceptible staphylococcal TSS, select nafcillin or oxacillin and clindamycin; for ",
{
"type":"abbreviation",
"title":"methicillin-resistant Staphylococcus aureus",
"children":[
"MRSA"
]
},
" TSS, select vancomycin and clindamycin."
]
},
{
"type":"heading",
"class":"tricked",
"children":[
"Don't Be Tricked"
]
},
{
"type":"list",
"class":"tricked",
"children":[
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"6ce347",
"children":[
"Do not select glucocorticoids to treat TSS."
]
},
" "
]
}
]
},
{
"type":"section",
"id":"mk19_bb_id_s7_3",
"title":{
"__html":"Test Yourself"
},
"titleNode":{
"type":"section-title",
"hlId":"7866cc",
"children":[
"Test Yourself"
]
},
"children":[
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"ae2c34",
"class":"test",
"children":[
"A 25-year-old man has epistaxis managed by nasal packing. The next day, he is confused, his temperature is 39.0 °C (102.2 °F), and ",
{
"type":"abbreviation",
"title":"blood pressure",
"children":[
"BP"
]
},
" is 90/82 mm Hg. Erythema of his face, shoulders, and palms is present. The nasal packing is still in place. Serum creatinine and aminotransferase levels are elevated."
]
},
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"312406",
"class":"test_answer",
"children":[
{
"type":"tag",
"tagName":"b",
"attrs":{
},
"children":[
"Answer:"
]
},
" ",
"For diagnosis, select staphylococcal TSS; for management, choose removal of the nasal packing and initiation of antibiotics."
]
}
]
}
]
